claim: The stem of a Herbaceous plant survives at the end of the growing season.
premise_source_doc_sentence: Herbaceous perennial and biennial plants may have stems that die at the end of the growing season , but parts of the plant survive under or close to the ground from season to season  (  for biennials , until the next growing season , when they flower and die  )  .
